36#include "kadm5_locl.h"
37
38__RCSID("$NetBSD: rename_s.c,v 1.2 2017/01/28 21:31:49 christos Exp $");
39
40kadm5_ret_t
41kadm5_s_rename_principal(void *server_handle,
42 krb5_principal source,
43 krb5_principal target)
44{
45 kadm5_server_context *context = server_handle;
46 kadm5_ret_t ret;
47 hdb_entry_ex ent;
48 krb5_principal oldname;
49
50 memset(&ent, 0, sizeof(ent));
51 if (krb5_principal_compare(context->context, source, target))
52 return KADM5_DUP; /* XXX is this right? */
53 if (!context->keep_open) {
54 ret = context->db->hdb_open(context->context, context->db, O_RDWR, 0);
55 if(ret)
56 return ret;
57 }
58
59 ret = kadm5_log_init(context);
60 if (ret)
61 goto out;
62
63 ret = context->db->hdb_fetch_kvno(context->context, context->db,
64 source, HDB_F_GET_ANY|HDB_F_ADMIN_DATA, 0, &ent);
65 if (ret)
66 goto out2;
67 oldname = ent.entry.principal;
68 ret = _kadm5_set_modifier(context, &ent.entry);
69 if (ret)
70 goto out3;
71 {
72 /* fix salt */
73 size_t i;
74 Salt salt;
75 krb5_salt salt2;
76 memset(&salt, 0, sizeof(salt));
77 krb5_get_pw_salt(context->context, source, &salt2);
78 salt.type = hdb_pw_salt;
79 salt.salt = salt2.saltvalue;
80 for(i = 0; i < ent.entry.keys.len; i++){
81 if(ent.entry.keys.val[i].salt == NULL){
82 ent.entry.keys.val[i].salt =
83 malloc(sizeof(*ent.entry.keys.val[i].salt));
84 if (ent.entry.keys.val[i].salt == NULL)
85 ret = ENOMEM;
86 else
87 ret = copy_Salt(&salt, ent.entry.keys.val[i].salt);
88 if (ret)
89 break;
90 }
91 }
92 krb5_free_salt(context->context, salt2);
93 }
94 if (ret)
95 goto out3;
96
97 /* Borrow target */
98 ent.entry.principal = target;
99 ret = hdb_seal_keys(context->context, context->db, &ent.entry);
100 if (ret)
101 goto out3;
102
103 /* This logs the change for iprop and writes to the HDB */
104 ret = kadm5_log_rename(context, source, &ent.entry);
105
106 out3:
107 ent.entry.principal = oldname; /* Unborrow target */
108 hdb_free_entry(context->context, &ent);
109
110 out2:
111 (void) kadm5_log_end(context);
112 out:
113 if (!context->keep_open) {
114 kadm5_ret_t ret2;
115 ret2 = context->db->hdb_close(context->context, context->db);
116 if (ret == 0 && ret2 != 0)
117 ret = ret2;
118 }
119 return _kadm5_error_code(ret);
120}
